I wish I had a clue about how AI will transform the world, but the nature of it makes it unpredictable. All I know is that our generation is staring into the abyss, about to jump in.

Seeing as how it's inevitable, I for one welcome our new AI overlords.

/End

Such a future elicits excitement and fear because of how unknown it is. Technology will advance at breakneck speeds, but human society will be left clueless for how to deal with all the change. Will the progress be enough to overcome societal upheaval?

/12

Many predicted that it wouldn't be for another 20-30 years before we reach some kind of AI singularity, but it's quite obvious that we are much closer to that reality -- and with it, perhaps the death of human purpose.

/11

What is the point in learning various skills if you can just ask an AI to do it for you at a master-level? I know I'd still  make an effort to learn new things because I'm wired that way, but when such an effective shortcut is available, who is going to take the long road?

/10

As a father of two boys, this has me feeling both excited and nihilistic about their futures. An AI empowered future has tons of promise for a better world, but if it's too good, what the hell are we, and especially our children, going to fucking do?! 

/9

With each generation of AI, it will enable more and more expert level skills to be democratized. This will both empower human creativity and productivity but will also make our main job in this new world be quality curating market participants, whose efforts only help the AI.

/8

Crypto was already moving so fast that it became impossible to keep up. Now it will move even faster. 

Great ü´°

Oh, but now it won't just be crypto, it'll be all fields moving faster than ever. 

/7

While the prospects of thousands of dapps being released every year is daunting, I'm sure we'll see some really cool stuff created by chatgpt empowered builders. 

/6

Conversely, this may be a good thing because these low effort cloners can now also be low effort innovators, now being empowered to put their own unique spin on the dapp mechanics. 

Buckle up bc the euthenasia roller coaster is gonna kick up a gear.

/5

We've already seen this in crypto because of our open source ethos -- which unfortunately leads to a LOT of low effort clones. Well, now the barrier to entry is even lower, as chatgpt will write your deploy script for you now too. 

/4

Usually jobs are gated by skill level, requiring one either learn the skill or hire someone to do it, but with chatgpt, no talent ass clowns will be able to produce at a high level (if their prompting is good enough). 

This will lead to an explosion of productivity 

/3

I'm sure you all know enough about chatgpt by now, but suffice to say, it already is at a level that can make large swathes of human labor redundant. Most impressively to me, it can do tasks such as PR statements, paperwork, creative writing, coding, and scientific discourse

/2

I'm both excited and terrified of our AI future.

Chatgpt is already essentially an undergraduate-pevel student in every domain of human knowledge, and if you believe Sam Altman, gpt4 will be an order of magnitude better -- and can self improve. 

1/13

Much like how life didn't evolve single cellular organisms to be giant monoliths, blockchains won't either. To scale they must become modular, or multicellular in a sense, which is why I'm big on ETH and am tuning into the Cosmos ecosystem.

I think the centralization tradeoffs to enable a high throughput monolithic chain are too costly to accept. I don't want to *have* to trust the handful of chain operators. It must be sufficiently decentralized to where that is a non-concern.

Tendermint chains can experiment with other models to enhance their security. For example, Celestia will be a data-availability layer for both rollups and Tendermint chains to hook into. Much like how Ethereum secures rollups, Celestia can enhance the security of tendy chains.

Cosmos chains trade off some security for their sovereignty. Anything running on Ethereum inherits the 100bln MC of ETH to help secure it from attacks. Whereas an app specific (or alt-evm l1) chain has much less tokenomic security and a much smaller validator set.

For when you want your application to run on a sovereign chain, Tendermint cosmos SDK is a powerful framework. Bootstrap a couple hundred validating nodes and veni vidi vici you have a blockchain that can talk to other like-chains. Even better, you can choose to run the EVM.

While rust development has seen some intake with Solana and Tendermint, the EVM has become the standard for smart contracts. EVM chains took off bc of all the open source advancements made on ETH mainnet. The gap will widen as we continue to improve our knowledge base and tooling

The future roadmap of Ethereum is broad and ambitious, but WHEN delivered, it will enable a connected, secure ecosystem with minimal friction to navigate the various rollups, with even some possibility for cross roll-up composibility, utilizing the strength of the ecosystem.

Ethereum is THE innovation hub, it's at the forefront of tokens, DeFi and NFTs. It and its dapps have a quality and liquidity factor an order of magnitude above its peers. Rollups scale this ecosystem into more scalable layers that enable new capabilities.

Ethereum and Tendermint (cosmos) are the fundamental technologies of web 3.
